- Closed: 2026-01-05T23:42:03Z   ...    The extensions that are present in ~/.pi/agent/extensions/my_extension follows the package.json + index.ts But in contrast to that if we add extension via settings.json, they only check index.ts and not package.json even if   ...    Ideally they should be consistent.

See this: To make configured directory paths respect `package.json` (so you can drop `index.ts`), you only need to change `discoverAndLoadExtensions` to *expand configured dirs* into explicit entry files. Right now, this line just passes the directory through: ```
addPaths(configuredPaths.map((p) => resolvePath(p, cwd)));
``` Replace it with logic like this in `../pi-mono/packages/coding-agent/src/core/extensions/loader.ts`: ```ts
// 3. Explicitly configured paths
for (const p of configuredPaths) {
  const resolved = resolvePath(p, cwd); if (fs.existsSync(resolved) && fs.statSync(resolved).isDirectory()) { const packageJsonPath = path.join(resolved, "package.json"); const manifest = fs.existsSync(packageJsonPath) ? readPiManifest(packageJsonPath) : null; if (manifest?.extensions?.length) {
      addPaths(manifest.extensions.map((ext) => path.resolve(resolved, ext)));   ...    if (fs.existsSync(indexJs)) { addPaths([indexJs]); continue; }
  } addPaths([resolved]);
}
```

Why this fixes it: - If you configure `"/path/to/extension"` it will read its `package.json` and load correctly - It *won’t* scan the directory for all `.ts` files (which would incorrectly load `extension-core.ts`, etc.). ---

